.:: Puzzle 4x4-Level-4-3::.
4 different games are played: snooker, bridge, mah-jongg, whist
The people have 4 different jobs:  librarian, paramedic, social-worker, writer
4 different brands of cigars are smoked: old-henry, chaman, dannemann, bongani
There 4 different types of food: blueberry, eggplant, strawberry, nectarine
 1. the person playing snooker is on the left or right of the librarian##3
 2. the chaman-smoker is the social-worker##1
 3. the person playing snooker is on the left or right of the person playing mah-jongg##3
 4. the librarian is on the right of the person eating nectarine##1
 5. the person playing bridge is the writer##1
 6. the person playing whist is on the left of the person eating eggplant##1
 7. the person eating blueberry is the bongani-smoker##1
 8. the writer is in an even position##4
 9. the person playing mah-jongg is on the left of the old-henry-smoker##1
10. the person eating blueberry is the person playing mah-jongg##1
11. the person playing snooker is in an odd position##4

.:: Answer ::.
|               |       1       |     2     |     3     |     4      |
| Game      | snooker | mah-jongg   | whist    | bridge      |
| Job           | social-worker | librarian | paramedic | writer     |
| Cigar   | chaman      | bongani   | old-henry   | dannemann |
| Food           | nectarine         | blueberry       | strawberry  | eggplant       |

